data.title: Enter the Dragons
data.description: Ushering in the 2-2-2 meta early in Stage 3 and capping it off with a Stage Final win, the Shanghai Dragons are confident that Stage 4 is where the Dragons will breathe the most fire.

data.title: Tactics: How the Shanghai Dragons set up a Pharah Barrage for DDing
data.description: Pharah's Barrage is capable of making explosive plays, but it's a tricky ultimate to use properly. Using Barrage leaves Pharah vulnerable to counterattacks, so she relies a lot on her teammates to land a good one. In this episode of Tactics, we break down a moment from the Shanghai Dragons' Stage 3 Playoffs victory, where every one of the Dragons goes above and beyond to set their Pharah player, DDing, up for a teamfight-winning Barrage. It's all part of Insights: powered by Intel. Want more Insights? Visit https://overwatchleague.com/en-us/intel-insights.

data.title: Looking to 2020
data.description: Nine players, nine cities, and one goal. We sat down with players from all around the world and discussed how excited they are to be playing in their home cities for the 2020 Overwatch League season.

data.title: Did You Catch That? The Mei Blizzard that ALMOST iced the Shock!
data.description: The 2019 Overwatch League Grand Finals featured some of the most harrowing clutch plays in the game's history. One of these moments featured San Francisco Shock's Rascal scoring a quintuple kill against the Vancouver Titans on the tail end of a teamfight that look doomed for the Shock. In this episode of, "Did You Catch That?", we break down how Rascal may not have been able to pull off this miracle play if the Titans had used their Mei ultimate just a little bit differently.

data.title: Tactics: Bastion ROCKET JUMPS onto a chandelier!
data.description: During the 2019 Grand Finals, the San Francisco Shock's Architect blew the crowd's minds as Bastion when he used his own rockets to blast himself up to a chandelier to win a teamfight vs. the Vancouver Titans. In this episode of Tactics, we examine why and how Architect pulled this move off and how it created an advantage for his team in the ensuing fight.

data.title: Overwatch League on the Red Carpet
data.description: When you work and play in Los Angeles, it’s not hard to find yourself brushing elbows with the stars! Follow the journey of several of our Overwatch League players as they donned their finest threads and strolled the red carpet for Variety’s Power of Young Hollywood party.
